DOM-WebGLActiveInfo-size.name: size
DOM-WebGLActiveInfo-size.summary: The read-only WebGLActiveInfo.size property is a Number representing the size of the requested data returned by calling the getActiveAttrib() or getActiveUniform() methods.

DOM-WebGLActiveInfo-type.name: type
DOM-WebGLActiveInfo-type.summary: The read-only WebGLActiveInfo.type property represents the type of the requested data returned by calling the getActiveAttrib() or getActiveUniform() methods.

5.11.name: WebGLActiveInfo

5.4.name: WebGLBuffer

5.15.1.name: statusMessage

5.15.1.title: WebGLContextEvent.statusMessage

5.15.name: WebGLContextEvent
5.15.summary: The WebContextEvent interface is part of the WebGL API and is an interface for an event that is generated in response to a status change to the WebGL rendering context.
5.15.title: WebGLContextEvent

5.5.name: WebGLFramebuffer
5.5.summary: The WebGLFramebuffer interface is part of the WebGL API and represents a collection of buffers that serve as a rendering destination.
5.5.title: WebGLFramebuffer

5.6.name: WebGLProgram
5.6.summary: The WebGLProgram is part of the WebGL API and is a combination of two compiled WebGLShaders consisting of a vertex shader and a fragment shader (both written in GLSL).
5.6.title: WebGLProgram

5.7.name: WebGLRenderbuffer
5.7.summary: The WebGLRenderbuffer interface is part of the WebGL API and represents a buffer that can contain an image, or can be source or target of an rendering operation.
5.7.title: WebGLRenderbuffer

5.14.3.name: activeTexture
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.activeTexture() method of the WebGL API specifies which texture unit to make active.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.activeTexture()

5.14.3.name: blendColor
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.blendColor() method of the WebGL API is used to set the source and destination blending factors.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.blendColor()

5.14.3.name: blendEquation
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.blendEquation() method of the WebGL API is used to set both the RGB blend equation and alpha blend equation to a single equation.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.blendEquation()

5.14.3.name: blendEquationSeparate
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.blendEquationSeparate() method of the WebGL API is used to set the RGB blend equation and alpha blend equation separately.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.blendEquationSeparate()

5.14.3.name: blendFunc
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.blendFunc() method of the WebGL API defines which function is used for blending pixel arithmetic.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.blendFunc()

5.14.3.name: blendFuncSeparate
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.blendFuncSeparate() method of the WebGL API defines which function is used for blending pixel arithmetic for RGB and alpha components separately.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.blendFuncSeparate()

5.14.3.name: clearColor
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.clearColor() method of the WebGL API specifies the color values used when clearing color buffers.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.clearColor()

5.14.3.name: clearDepth
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.clearDepth() method of the WebGL API specifies the clear value for the depth buffer.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.clearDepth()

5.14.3.name: clearStencil
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.clearStencil() method of the WebGL API specifies the clear value for the stencil buffer.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.clearStencil()

5.14.3.name: colorMask
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.colorMask() method of the WebGL API sets which color components to enable or to disable when drawing or rendering to a WebGLFramebuffer.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.colorMask()

5.14.3.name: cullFace
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.cullFace() method of the WebGL API specifies whether or not front- and/or back-facing polygons can be culled.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.cullFace()

5.14.3.name: depthFunc
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.depthFunc() method of the WebGL API specifies a function that compares incoming pixel depth to the current depth buffer value.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.depthFunc()

5.14.3.name: depthMask
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.depthMask() method of the WebGL API sets whether writing into the depth buffer is enabled or disabled.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.depthMask()

5.14.3.name: depthRange
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.depthRange() method of the WebGL API specifies the depth range mapping from normalized device coordinates to window or viewport coordinates.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.depthRange()

5.14.3.name: disable
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.disable() method of the WebGL API disables specific WebGL capabilities for this context.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.disable()

5.14.3.name: enable
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.enable() method of the WebGL API enables specific WebGL capabilities for this context.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.enable()

5.14.3.name: frontFace
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.frontFace() method of the WebGL API specifies whether polygons are front- or back-facing by setting a winding orientation.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.frontFace()

5.14.3.name: getError
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.getError() method of the WebGL API returns error information.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.getError()

5.14.3.name: getParameter
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.getParameter() method of the WebGL API returns a value for the passed parameter name.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.getParameter()

5.14.3.name: hint
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.hint() method of the WebGL API specifies hints for certain behaviors. The interpretation of these hints depend on the implementation.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.hint()

5.14.3.name: isEnabled
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.isEnabled() method of the WebGL API tests whether a specific WebGL capability is enabled or not for this context.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.isEnabled()

5.14.3.name: lineWidth
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.lineWidth() method of the WebGL API sets the line width of rasterized lines.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.lineWidth()

5.14.3.name: pixelStorei
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.pixelStorei() method of the WebGL API specifies the pixel storage modes.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.pixelStorei()

5.14.3.name: polygonOffset
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.polygonOffset() method of the WebGL API specifies the scale factors and units to calculate depth values.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.polygonOffset()

5.14.3.name: sampleCoverage
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.sampleCoverage() method of the WebGL API specifies multi-sample coverage parameters for anti-aliasing effects.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.sampleCoverage()

5.14.3.name: stencilFunc
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.stencilFunc() method of the WebGL API sets the front and back function and reference value for stencil testing.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.stencilFunc()

5.14.3.name: stencilFuncSeparate
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.stencilFuncSeparate() method of the WebGL API sets the front and/or back function and reference value for stencil testing.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.stencilFuncSeparate()

5.14.3.name: stencilMask
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.stencilMask() method of the WebGL API controls enabling and disabling of both the front and back writing of individual bits in the stencil planes.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.stencilMask()

5.14.3.name: stencilMaskSeparate
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.stencilMaskSeparate() method of the WebGL API controls enabling and disabling of front and/or back writing of individual bits in the stencil planes.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.stencilMaskSeparate()

5.14.3.name: stencilOp
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.stencilOp() method of the WebGL API sets both the front and back-facing stencil test actions.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.stencilOp()

5.14.3.name: stencilOpSeparate
5.14.3.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.stencilOpSeparate() method of the WebGL API sets the front and/or back-facing stencil test actions.
5.14.3.title: WebGLRenderingContext.stencilOpSeparate()

5.14.9.name: attachShader
5.14.9.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.attachShader() method of the WebGL API attaches either a fragment or vertex WebGLShader to a WebGLProgram.
5.14.9.title: WebGLRenderingContext.attachShader()

5.14.9.name: bindAttribLocation
5.14.9.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.bindAttribLocation() method of the WebGL API binds a generic vertex index to an attribute variable.
5.14.9.title: WebGLRenderingContext.bindAttribLocation()

5.14.9.name: compileShader
5.14.9.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.compileShader() method of the WebGL API compiles a GLSL shader into binary data so that it can be used by a WebGLProgram.
5.14.9.title: WebGLRenderingContext.compileShader()

5.14.9.name: createProgram
5.14.9.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.createProgram() method of the WebGL API creates and initializes a WebGLProgram object.
5.14.9.title: WebGLRenderingContext.createProgram()

5.14.9.name: createShader

5.14.9.title: WebGLRenderingContext.createShader()

5.14.9.name: deleteProgram
5.14.9.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.deleteProgram() method of the WebGL API deletes a given WebGLProgram object. This method has no effect if the program has already been deleted.
5.14.9.title: WebGLRenderingContext.deleteProgram()

5.14.9.name: deleteShader
5.14.9.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.deleteShader() method of the WebGL API marks a given WebGLShader object for deletion. It will then be deleted whenever the shader is no longer in use. This method has no effect if the shader has already been deleted, and the WebGLShader is automatically marked for deletion when it is destroyed by the garbage collector.
5.14.9.title: WebGLRenderingContext.deleteShader()

5.14.9.name: detachShader

5.14.9.title: WebGLRenderingContext.detachShader()

5.14.9.title: WebGLRenderingContext.getAttachedShaders()

5.14.9.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.getProgramInfoLog returns the information log for the specified WebGLProgram object. It contains errors that occurred during failed linking or validation of WebGLProgram objects.
5.14.9.title: WebGLRenderingContext.getProgramInfoLog()

5.14.9.name: getProgramParameter
5.14.9.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.getProgramParameter() method of the WebGL API returns information about the given program.
5.14.9.title: WebGLRenderingContext.getProgramParameter()

5.14.9.name: getShaderInfoLog
5.14.9.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.getShaderInfoLog returns the information log for the specified WebGLShader object. It contains warnings, debugging and compile information.

5.14.9.name: getShaderParameter

5.14.9.title: WebGLRenderingContext.getShaderParameter()

5.14.9.name: getShaderPrecisionFormat

5.14.9.name: isProgram

5.14.9.name: useProgram

5.14.9.title: WebGLRenderingContext.useProgram()

5.14.9.name: validateProgram
5.14.9.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.validateProgram() method of the WebGL API validates a WebGLProgram. It checks if it is successfully linked and if it can be used in the current WebGL state.

5.14.5.name: bindBuffer

5.14.7.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.bindRenderbuffer() method of the WebGL API binds a given WebGLRenderbuffer to a target, which must be gl.RENDERBUFFER.

5.14.7.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.createRenderbuffer() method of the WebGL API creates and initializes a WebGLRenderbuffer object.

5.14.7.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.getRenderbufferParameter() method of the WebGL API returns information about the renderbuffer.

5.14.7.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.isRenderbuffer() method of the WebGL API returns true if the passed WebGLRenderbuffer is valid and false otherwise.

5.14.10.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.getUniform() method of the WebGL API returns the value of a uniform variable at a given location.

5.14.10.name: getUniformLocation
5.14.10.summary: Part of the WebGL API, the WebGLRenderingContext method getUniformLocation() returns the location of a specific uniform variable which is part of a given WebGLProgram.

5.14.10.name: getVertexAttrib

5.14.10.name: getVertexAttribOffset

5.14.10.name: uniform1f
5.14.10.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.uniform[1234][fi][v]() methods of the WebGL API specify values of uniform variables. All active uniform variables defined in a program object are initialized to 0 when the program object is linked successfully. They retain the values assigned to them by a call to this method until the next successful link operation occurs on the program object, when they are once again initialized to 0.
5.14.10.title: WebGLRenderingContext.uniform[1234][fi][v]()

5.14.10.name: vertexAttribPointer
5.14.10.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.vertexAttribPointer() method of the WebGL API binds the buffer currently bound to gl.ARRAY_BUFFER to a generic vertex attribute of the current vertex buffer object and specifies its layout.

DOM-WebGLRenderingContext-drawingBufferH.name: drawingBufferHeight
DOM-WebGLRenderingContext-drawingBufferH.summary: The read-only WebGLRenderingContext.drawingBufferHeight property represents the actual height of the current drawing buffer. It should match the height attribute of the <canvas> element associated with this context, but might differ if the implementation is not able to provide the requested height.
DOM-WebGLRenderingContext-drawingBufferH.title: WebGLRenderingContext.drawingBufferHeight

DOM-WebGLRenderingContext-drawingBufferW.name: drawingBufferWidth
DOM-WebGLRenderingContext-drawingBufferW.summary: The read-only WebGLRenderingContext.drawingBufferWidth property represents the actual width of the current drawing buffer. It should match the width attribute of the <canvas> element associated with this context, but might differ if the implementation is not able to provide the requested width.
DOM-WebGLRenderingContext-drawingBufferW.title: WebGLRenderingContext.drawingBufferWidth

5.14.2.name: getContextAttributes
5.14.2.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.getContextAttributes() method returns a WebGLContextAttributes object that contains the actual context parameters. Might return null, if the context is lost.
5.14.2.title: WebGLRenderingContext.getContextAttributes()

5.14.14.name: getExtension
5.14.14.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.getExtension() method enables a WebGL extension.
5.14.14.title: WebGLRenderingContext.getExtension()

5.14.14.name: getSupportedExtensions
5.14.14.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.getSupportedExtensions() method returns a list of all the supported WebGL extensions.
5.14.14.title: WebGLRenderingContext.getSupportedExtensions()

5.14.13.name: isContextLost
5.14.13.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.isContextLost() method returns a Boolean indicating whether or not the WebGL context has been lost and must be re-established before rendering can resume.
5.14.13.title: WebGLRenderingContext.isContextLost()

PIXEL_STORAGE_PARAMETERS.name: pixelStorei
PIXEL_STORAGE_PARAMETERS.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.pixelStorei() method of the WebGL API specifies the pixel storage modes.
PIXEL_STORAGE_PARAMETERS.title: WebGLRenderingContext.pixelStorei()

5.14.12.name: readPixels
5.14.12.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.readPixels() method of the WebGL API reads a block of pixels from a specified rectangle of the current color framebuffer into an ArrayBufferView object.
5.14.12.title: WebGLRenderingContext.readPixels()

5.14.4.name: scissor
5.14.4.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.scissor() method of the WebGL API sets a scissor box, which limits the drawing to a specified rectangle.
5.14.4.title: WebGLRenderingContext.scissor()

5.14.4.name: viewport
5.14.4.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.viewport() method of the WebGL API sets the viewport, which specifies the affine transformation of x and y from normalized device coordinates to window coordinates.
5.14.4.title: WebGLRenderingContext.viewport()

TEXSUBIMAGE2D.name: texSubImage2D
TEXSUBIMAGE2D.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext.texSubImage2D() method of the WebGL API specifies a sub-rectangle of the current texture.
TEXSUBIMAGE2D.title: WebGLRenderingContext.texSubImage2D()

5.14.name: WebGLRenderingContext
5.14.summary: The WebGLRenderingContext interface provides an interface to the OpenGL ES 2.0 graphics rendering context for the drawing surface of an HTML <canvas> element.

ie.notes: To access the WebGL context, use experimental-webgl rather than the standard webgl identifier.

5.14.title: WebGLRenderingContext

5.8.name: WebGLShader
5.8.summary: The WebGLShader is part of the WebGL API and can either be a vertex or a fragment shader. A WebGLProgram requires both types of shaders.
5.8.title: WebGLShader

DOM-WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat-precision.name: precision
DOM-WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat-precision.summary: The read-only WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat.precision property returns the number of bits of precision that can be represented.
DOM-WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat-precision.title: WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat.precision

DOM-WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat-rangeMax.name: rangeMax
DOM-WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat-rangeMax.summary: The read-only WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat.rangeMax property returns the base 2 log of the absolute value of the maximum value that can be represented.
DOM-WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat-rangeMax.title: WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat.rangeMax

DOM-WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat-rangeMin.name: rangeMin
DOM-WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat-rangeMin.summary: The read-only WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat.rangeMin property returns the base 2 log of the absolute value of the minimum value that can be represented.
DOM-WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat-rangeMin.title: WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat.rangeMin

5.12.name: WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat
5.12.summary: The WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat interface is part of the WebGL API and represents the information returned by calling the WebGLRenderingContext.getShaderPrecisionFormat() method.
5.12.title: WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat

5.9.name: WebGLTexture
5.9.summary: The WebGLTexture interface is part of the WebGL API and represents an opaque texture object providing storage and state for texturing operations.
5.9.title: WebGLTexture

5.10.name: WebGLUniformLocation
5.10.summary: The WebGLUniformLocation interface is part of the WebGL API and represents the location of a uniform variable in a shader program.
5.10.title: WebGLUniformLocation
